Review_Text: The film feels really hollow. It felt like the duo directors were trying to find a story where there wasn't a story. The cinematography made the doc feel slow but you can tell there's some talent behind the lens. There just isn't an interesting story here.

Review_title: An incomplete documentary with very little to say
Review_Text: I don't understand why this needed to be made. It's about an hour long, so not even really a feature-length film. I didn't really like it at all. Strike two for Hodgee Films, because Pharma Bro was bad too.
